@sanyam: My friend... I have in the past, but...
It is pretty unique "way", strange to all people who are (let face it) a "consumers", with little (or less) knowledge about encoding, formats, how, which, when and so forth.

Every time I've done that it turned out to be mistake, and instead of putting what's left of my energy in finding and encoding, transformed my work into "Howto" do that or this, in some sort of audio-video forum/questionnaire - what this place (and my old "home") definitely is not and never become one.
